The paper proposes a novel approach for deep reinforcement learning with constraints, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach is applied to robotics locomotive tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions using data generated from the current policy, which suggests the use of computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
